Anatomist				KEY:Anatomist_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You have studied the workings of anatomy, either as a student at university or as an apprentice mortician or necromancer.																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Armor Expert			KEY:Armor Expert_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You have worn armor as long as you can remember, either as part of your training to become a knight's squire or simply because you were seeking to emulate a hero.																																																															BONUS:MISC|ACCHECK|1																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Bullied				KEY:Bullied_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were bullied often as a child, and you are now constantly ready to defend yourself with your fists when an enemy comes near.																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Courageous				KEY:Courageous_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your childhood was brutal, yet you persevered primarily through force of will and the hope that no matter how hard things might get, as long as you kept a level head you'd make it through.																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Deft Dodger				KEY:Deft Dodger_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Growing up in a rough neighborhood or a dangerous environment has honed your senses.																																																																																BONUS:SAVE|Reflex|1|TYPE=Trait																																SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Dirty Fighter			KEY:Dirty Fighter_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You wouldn't have lived to make it out of childhood without the aid of a sibling, friend, or companion on whom you could always count to distract your enemies long enough to do a little bit more damage than normal.																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Fencer				KEY:Fencer_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You trained long hours as a youth with blades, either taking lessons in the genteel art of fencing from tutors paid for by your parents or by being taken under the wing of a disenfranchised fencer who may have turned to a life of crime.																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Killer				KEY:Killer_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You made your first kill at a very young age and found the task of war or murder to your liking.																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Reactionary				KEY:Reactionary_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were bullied often as a child, but never quite developed an offensive response. Instead, you became adept at anticipating sudden attacks and reacting to danger quickly.																																																						BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|2|TYPE=Trait																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Resilient				KEY:Resilient_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Growing up in a violent neighborhood or in the unforgiving wilds often forced you to subsist on food and water from doubtful sources.																																																																							BONUS:SAVE|Fortitude|1|TYPE=Trait																																SOURCEPAGE:p.4

# Faith Traits
Birthmark				KEY:Birthmark_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were born with a strange birthmark that looks very similar to the holy symbol of the god you chose to worship later in life.																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Caretaker				KEY:Caretaker_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:As the child of an herbalist or an assistant in a temple infirmary, you often had to assist in tending to the sick and wounded.																																																																														BONUS:SKILL|Heal|1|TYPE=Trait																		CSKILL:Heal								SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Child of the Temple		KEY:Child of the Temple_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You have long served at a temple in a city, and not only did you pick up on many of the nobility's customs, you spent much time in the temple libraries studying your faith.																											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILL|Knowledge (Nobility and Royalty)|Knowledge (Religion)																											BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Nobility and Royalty),Knowledge (Religion)|1|TYPE=Trait									CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Devotee of the Green		KEY:Devotee of the Green_Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your faith in the natural world or one of the gods of nature makes it easy for you to pick up on related concepts.																																					STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILL|Knowledge (Geography)|Knowledge (Nature)																													BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Geography),Knowledge (Nature)|1|TYPE=Trait												CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Ease of Faith			KEY:Ease of Faith_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your mentor, the person who invested your faith in you from an early age, took steps to ensure that you understood that what powers your divine magic is no different than that which powers the magic of other religions.																																																															BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Diplomacy							SOURCEPAGE:p.4
History of Heresy			KEY:History of Heresy_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were raised with heretical views that have made it not only difficult for you to accept most religious beliefs, but you also have had to live with the fact that you or those you love were often treated as pariahs.																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.4
Indomitable Faith			KEY:Indomitable Faith_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were born in a region where your faith was not popular, yet you never abandoned it.																																																																															BONUS:SAVE|Will|1|TYPE=Trait																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Sacred Conduit			KEY:Sacred Conduit_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your birth was particularly painful and difficult for your mother, who needed potent divine magic to ensure you survived; your mother may or may not have survived. In any event, the magic infused you from an early age, and you now channel divine energy with greater ease than most.																																																																				BONUS:VAR|TurnCheckUndead|2|TYPE=Trait										SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Sacred Touch			KEY:Sacred Touch_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were exposed to a potent source of positive energy as a child, perhaps by being born under the right cosmic sign, or maybe because one of your parents was a gifted healer.																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Scholar of the Great Beyond	KEY:Scholar of the Great Beyond_Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your great interests as a child did not lie with current events or the mundane-- you have always felt out of place, as if you were born in the wrong era.																														STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILL|Knowledge (History)|Knowledge (the planes)																													BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (History),Knowledge (The Planes)|1|TYPE=Trait											CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p.5

# Magic Traits
Classically Schooled		KEY:Classically Schooled_Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your apprenticeship or early education was particularly focused on the direct application of magic.																																																																																			BONUS:SKILL|Spellcraft|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Spellcraft							SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Dangerously Curious		KEY:Dangerously Curious_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You have always been intrigued by magic, possibly because you were the child of a magician or priest. You often snuck into your parent's laboratory or shrine to tinker with spell components and magic devices, and often caused quite a bit of damage and headaches for your parent as a result.																																																			BONUS:SKILL|Use Magic Device|1|TYPE=Trait																CSKILL:Use Magic Device						SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Focused Mind			KEY:Focused Mind_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your childhood was either dominated by lessons of some sort (be they musical or academic) or by a horrible home life that encouraged your ability to block out distractions to focus on the immediate task at hand.																																																																BONUS:SKILL|Concentration|1|TYPE=Trait																CSKILL:Concentration						SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Gifted Adept			KEY:Gifted Adept_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your interest in magic was inspired by witnessing a spell being cast in a particularly dramatic method, perhaps even one that affected you physically or spiritually.																												STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SPELLS|SPELLTYPE=Arcane|SPELLTYPE=Divine							BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SPELL.%LIST|1																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Hedge Magician			KEY:Hedge Magician_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You apprenticed for a time to a craftsman who often built magic items, and he taught you many handy shortcuts and cost-saving techniques.																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Magical Knack			KEY:Magical Knack_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were raised, either wholly or in part, by a magical creature, either after it found you abandoned in the woods or because your parents often left you in the care of a magical minion. This constant exposure to magic has made its mysteries easy for you to understand, even when you turn your mind to other devotions and tasks.			MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|USERINPUT|TITLE=Class Name								SELECT:1	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|LIST|1																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Magical Lineage			KEY:Magical Lineage_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:One of your parents was a gifted spellcaster who not only used metamagic often, but developed many magical items and perhaps even a new spell or two--and you have inherited a fragment of this greatness.																								MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SPELLS|SPELLTYPE=Arcane|SPELLTYPE=Divine																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Magical Talent			KEY:Magical Talent_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Either from inborn talent, whimsy of the gods, or obsessive study of strange tomes, you have mastered the use of a cantrip.																																					MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SPELLS|SPELLTYPE=Arcane[LEVELMAX=0]|SPELLTYPE=Divine[LEVELMAX=0]																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Mathematical Prodigy		KEY:Mathematical Prodigy_Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Mathematics has always come easily for you, and you have always been able to "see the math" in the physical and magical world.																																			STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILL|Knowledge (Arcana)|Knowledge (Architecture and Engineering)																										BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Arcana),Knowledge (Architecture and Engineering)|1|TYPE=Trait								CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p.5
Skeptic				KEY:Skeptic_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Growing up, you were always around magical effects to the extent that you realized that much of it was smoke and mirrors.																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.5

# Social Traits
Adopted				KEY:Adopted_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were adopted and raised by someone not of your actual race, and raised in a society not your own.																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Bully					KEY:Bully_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You grew up in an environment where the meek were ignored and you often had to resort to threats or violence to be heard.																																																																															BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Intimidate							SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Canter				KEY:Canter_Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You grew up among thieves and scoundrels, and their unusual speech patterns and turns of phrase don't phase you in the slightest today as a result.																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Charming				KEY:Charming_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Blessed with good looks, you've come to depend on the fact that others find you attractive.																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Child of the Streets		KEY:Child of the Streets_Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You grew up on the streets of a large city, and as a result you have developed a knack of knowing where to go and who to talk to when you're looking for some information.																																																																							BONUS:SKILL|Gather Information|1|TYPE=Trait															CSKILL:Gather Information					SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Fast-Talker				KEY:Fast-Talker_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You had a knack at getting yourself into trouble as a child, and as a result developed a silver tongue at an early age.																																																																																BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Bluff							SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Natural-Born Leader		KEY:Natural-Born Leader_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You've always found yourself in positions where others look up to you as a leader, and you can distinctly remember an event from your early childhood where you led several other children to accomplish a goal that each of you individually could not.																																																																									BONUS:VAR|LeadershipScore|1|TYPE=Trait										SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Poverty-Stricken			KEY:Poverty-Stricken_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your childhood was tough, and your parents had to make every copper piece count. Hunger was your constant companion, and you often had to live off the land or sleep in the wild.																																																																						BONUS:SKILL|Survival|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Survival							SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Rich Parents			KEY:Rich Parents_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were born into a rich family, perhaps even the nobility.																																																																																																																					KIT:1|Rich Parents	SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Suspicious				KEY:Suspicious_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You discovered at an early age that someone you trusted, perhaps an older sibling or a parent, had lied to you, and often, about something you had taken for granted, leaving you quick to question the claims of others.																																																															BONUS:SKILL|Sense Motive|1|TYPE=Trait																CSKILL:Sense Motive						SOURCEPAGE:p.6

